{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":5285,"record_hash":"sha256:37b4a329227fa640380af7b2b60b00a4c8fed6f6cdb46346bbc09ce02361cae8","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:30:24.703Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 40012f\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1143\nOutput:\n# Capture Workflow\n\nThis document separates current explicit capture from future discovery. The POC\nworkflow is defined in [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md).\n\n## Current Boundary\n\nThe POC supports explicit capture:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture \\\n  --transcript-path <path> \\\n  [--agent <codex|claude>] \\\n  [--associate-target <target>]\n```\n\nIt should not infer the current session, scan the machine, serialize GitMeta, or\nguess branch ownership. The outer `but` CLI may detect the invoking agent from\nenvironment variables, but transcript selection remains explicit.\n`--associate-target` is an explicit relationship link, not inferred ownership.\nProvider working-directory fields are not stored in transcript records.\n\nThe POC also supports hook capture:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog hook \\\n  [--agent <codex|claude>] \\\n  [--associate-target <target>]\n```\n\n`agentlog hook` reads one hook JSON object from stdin, uses the hook\n`transcript_path` and `cwd`, and exits successfully without output when\n`transcript_path` is missing. Like `capture`, it may infer the agent from the\nouter `but` CLI's environment detection. After a successful capture, it starts\n`but agentlog sync` in the background.\n\n## Future Inputs\n\nLater capture can accept increasingly implicit inputs, in this order of\npreference:\n\n1. exact transcript path from a hook payload\n2. explicit provider session id\n3. agent-provided environment session id\n4. recent files in known agent directories, filtered by a later explicit\n   repository-matching strategy\n\nThe command should prefer no capture over capturing a plausible but unrelated\nsession.\n\n## Codex Discovery\n\nDo not implement discovery in the first POC.\n\nWhen added, resolve the Codex home directory as:\n\n1. `CODEX_HOME`, when set\n2. otherwise the user's home directory joined with `.codex`\n\nOn macOS and Linux this normally means `~/.codex`. On native Windows, use the\nWindows user profile\n[TRUNCATED]\ntime descending\n- inspect only enough early JSONL records to find session metadata\n- avoid storing local path fields from provider records\n- auto-select only when exactly one candidate matches\n- ask for `--transcript-path` when no candidate or several candidates match\n\n## Claude Discovery\n\nDo not implement discovery in the first POC.\n\nWhen added, resolve the Claude config directory as:\n\n1. `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR`, when set\n2. otherwise the user's home directory joined with `.claude`\n\nThen look under:\n\n```text\n<claude-config-dir>/projects/<encoded-cwd>/*.jsonl\n```\n\nThe encoded project path is provider-local and lossy; use it only to narrow\nfuture discovery candidates, never as stored agentlog data.\n\n## Freshness\n\nWhen no exact transcript path is provided, freshness should consider:\n\n- file modification time\n- session metadata timestamp\n- matching session id from an environment variable or hook payload\n- a configurable maximum age\n\n## Hook Usage\n\nHook usage relies on provider payloads that include the exact transcript path.\nBoth Claude Code and Codex command hooks provide `transcript_path` and `cwd` in\nthe JSON object sent on stdin.\n\nClaude Code project settings can run the quiet hook command from `Stop`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"hooks\": {\n    \"Stop\": [\n      {\n        \"hooks\": [\n          {\n            \"type\": \"command\",\n            \"command\": \"but agentlog hook\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCodex project config can do the same:\n\n```toml\n[features]\ncodex_hooks = true\n\n[[hooks.Stop]]\n[[hooks.Stop.hooks]]\ntype = \"command\"\ncommand = \"but agentlog hook\"\n```\n\nCodex `Stop` expects JSON on stdout when stdout is present, so the hook command\nmust stay silent on success. Claude Code also accepts silent successful command\nhooks. If a future hook needs to influence the agent, add a separate command\nrather than changing `agentlog hook` into an agent-control surface.\n\nReferences:\n\n- [Claude Code hooks reference](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks)\n- [Codex hooks reference](https://developers.openai.com/codex/hooks)\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:30:24.703Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}